# Session Kickoff Playbook

> **Anti-context-rot protocol.** Follow this at the start of every coding session
> to stay grounded in the codebase without blowing your context window.

---

## The 6-File Rule

**Maximum 6 files loaded before you start coding.**

Loading too many files causes context rot -- the AI loses track of earlier
information as the window fills. Six files is the sweet spot: enough to
understand the task, small enough to retain everything.

---

## File Loading Order

Load these files in this exact order:

| Priority | File | Why |
|----------|------|-----|
| 1 | `{{AI_CONFIG_FILE}}` | Project-wide rules, protect list, anti-patterns |
| 2 | Service hub (`services/{service}.md`) | Current service context, endpoints, screens |
| 3 | `STATUS.md` | Know what is in progress, what is blocked |
| 4 | Task file (`tasks/{task-id}.md`) | Specific acceptance criteria and file plan |
| 5 | Context file 1 (from task header) | Related source file or spec |
| 6 | Context file 2 (from task header) | Related source file or spec |

> If a task's Context Header lists more than 2 related files, pick the two
> most relevant. You can always load more later if needed.

---

## Session Start Protocol

```
1. Read {{AI_CONFIG_FILE}}
2. Read the service hub for today's work area
3. Read STATUS.md -- identify your task(s)
4. Read the task file -- understand acceptance criteria
5. Load up to 2 context files from the task header
6. Begin coding (you are now at 6 files)
```

### Before You Code, Verify:
- [ ] You know which task ID you are working on
- [ ] You have read the acceptance criteria
- [ ] You know the file plan (which files to create/edit)
- [ ] You checked dependencies -- nothing is blocking you
- [ ] You are NOT touching anything on the **Protect List**

---

## Session End Protocol

```
1. Update STATUS.md -- mark tasks as Done / In Progress / Blocked
2. Add a CHANGELOG.md entry (append-only, never edit old entries)
3. Commit all changes with a descriptive message
4. Note any blockers or follow-up items in the changelog entry
```

---

## Context Window Tips

| Tip | Rationale |
|-----|-----------|
| Prefer reading specific functions over entire files | Smaller reads = more room for reasoning |
| Use grep/search before reading | Find the right file first, read second |
| Summarize long files mentally before proceeding | Reduces re-reading later |
| Avoid loading test files unless you are writing tests | Tests are large and context-heavy |
| If you feel lost, re-read the task file | It is your north star for the session |
| Close finished contexts by moving to the next task | Do not carry stale file contents forward |

